annotationA: Translationally controlled tumor protein (Tctp) belongs to the TCTP family. It interacts with the GTPase Rheb to regulate organ growth. Tctp is required for DNA damage response and genome stability
annotationB: Ribosomal protein S15, isoform A; Structural constituent of ribosome; RNA binding. It is involved in the biological process described with: mitotic spindle elongation; translation; mitotic spindle organization; Belongs to the universal ribosomal protein uS19 family
